The paper proposes a transfer learning approach that involves learning transfer features and classifiers without the need for model selection and hyperparameter tuning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on classification tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning methods, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it could belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
